HEADWORD: Pinesap
<hw>Pine"sap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
reddish fleshy herb of the genus <gen>Monotropa</gen> (<spn>Monotropa
hypopitys</spn>), formerly thought to be parasitic on the roots of pine
trees, but more probably saprophytic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pine-tree State</ent>⟦br⟧
